Package io.crums.sldg.entry

Class Entry

java.lang.Object
io.crums.sldg.entry.Entry
Direct Known Subclasses:
Entry.IdentityHash, Entry.RuleBased, TextEntry
public class Entry
extends java.lang.Object
Source of a row's input hash. Note this may not always be practical. For example, if the source is the contents of a very large file, then an instance may not comfortably fit in memory.

Hashing Method

Instances of this class encode both the source of the ledger-row's input hash (see content()) and how that source is transformed into a hash. This is done implicitly thru the overridable hash() method: the base implementaion computes a straight hash of the contents. A subclass may employ more complex business rules. For example, if the contents is text, the hashing method may first hash each word separately, and then hash the sequence of hashes those words generated (that way, you could redact any word but still show the rest of the entry.)

Instances are immutable and safe under concurrent access.

      public java.nio.ByteBuffer hash()
